Date: 0/0/1933
Source: Reminiscences of Early Days
Author: WASHBOURN
Vol / Page: 12
Edition:
Quote: There were then [near the bush] millions of small flies which were known as `smoke flies' ... Most flies ... do not like smoke, but these seemed to delight in it and over a camp fire they would form a high column in the smoke. They did not bite or interfere in any way.
Notes: [c. 1857-1859]
